i8s.COM.w1: It was difficult to fill this out because the parent-child relationship is so fraught, and because people behave differently within their families of origin than with others.  I tried to answer the questions without taking them too personally.  For example, as the mother of a teenage daughter I have experienced her capacity for rudeness in a way others probably have not, but I answered more generally instead of simply reflecting on how I myself have been treated.

As Person X's parent, I see some of my responses as most likely applying only to my parental relationship and not how she interacts with others.  I view this as developmentally appropriate on her part.
